===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Charles Moncky|Charles Moncky]] who invented this wrench in 1858.

=== Noun ===
'''monkey wrench'''
# a [[wrench]], with a smooth adjustable jaw to grip different sizes of [[nut]]s.
#{{idiom}} a [[problem]], [[obstacle]] or [[dilemma]]; something [[unexpected]] or [[troublesome]]
#:''Having a baby will add a '''monkey wrench''' to her routines.''

